                <head>296. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On the evening of December 4, Averoff and <persName corresp="#p_ZFR1"
                        >Zorlu</persName> conferred and agreed on a compromise resolution on Cyprus
                    which was introduced in the General Assembly on December 5 by the Mexican
                    Representative. This resolution reaffirmed Resolution 1013 (XI) of the 12th
                    Session of the General Assembly and called upon the parties to “continue
                    efforts” to reach a just settlement in accordance with the U.N. Charter. This
                    resolution was adopted unanimously and without debate by the General Assembly on
                    December 5. For text of the Mexican resolution, see U.N. doc. A/Res/1287
                    (XIII).</p>
            </div>
